%% D02 · Orchestrator System detail
%% Answers: What are the six sub-responsibilities of the Orchestrator System and how do they compose?
%% Referenced in §06 Core Components.

flowchart LR
    IN["Incoming:<br/>Consensus Packets<br/>+ Memory Index<br/>+ Orchestrator State"]

    subgraph OS["Orchestrator System · Six Sub-Responsibilities"]
        direction TB
        CM["1 · Context Manager<br/>load right slice of memory<br/>enforce token budget<br/>summarize when needed"]
        BS["2 · BS Detector<br/>rubric-based hallucination /<br/>over-confidence flags<br/>LLM-judge, not guardrail"]
        VA["3 · Validator<br/>bridges to deterministic<br/>verifier tools<br/>pass / fail / abstain"]
        SN["4 · Signal/Noise Attributor<br/>weight emissions by:<br/>calibration, verifier,<br/>agreement, BS flags, authority"]
        WT["5 · Weight Tweaker<br/>update per-agent and<br/>per-tool trust weights<br/>from retrospective outcomes"]
        DD["6 · Drift Detector<br/>Signal A (cosine)<br/>+ Signal B (rubric)<br/>proceed / warn / pause / halt"]
    end

    OUT["Outgoing:<br/>Curated context<br/>+ Weighted claims<br/>+ Drift status<br/>to Primary Orchestrator"]

    IN --> CM
    CM --> BS
    BS --> VA
    VA --> SN
    SN --> WT
    CM --> DD
    DD --> OUT
    SN --> OUT
    WT -.->|"updates"| SN

    classDef inCls fill:#e8dccc,stroke:#5a4a3a,color:#2d2317
    classDef subCls fill:#f2ede4,stroke:#6b5d4a,color:#2d2317
    classDef outCls fill:#ede4d3,stroke:#7a6545,color:#2d2317

    class IN inCls
    class CM,BS,VA,SN,WT,DD subCls
    class OUT outCls
